QUESTIONS PASSED AS ORDERS FOR RETURNS

WHEAT SUB SIDIES

Mr. Fair:

1. During each of the crop years 1939-40 to date. how many bushels of wheat have been supplied to millers on which a subsidy has been paid?

2. During the same period, what quantity of wheat has been supplied to others on which a subsidy has been paid?

3. What is the amount of subsidy paid each crop year in each of the above classes?

Mr. Belzile: Return tabled.

following categories: (1) merchandise; (2) receipts by War Supplies Limited; (3) net exports of non- monetary gold; (4) tourist expenditures; (5) interest and dividends; (6) freight and shipping; (7) inheri- tance and immigration funds; (8) national defence; (9) all other current receipts and expenditures for (a) all countries; (b) United Kingdom; (c) other sterling areas; (d) United States of America; (e) all other countries?

Mr. Cockeram:

What were the amounts on capital account in the Canadian balance of international payments for the calendar year 1948 in each of the following cate- gories: (1) loans and net export credits; (2) gold subscriptions; (3) net receipts of convertible ex- change from overseas countries; (4) loan repay- ments; (5) sale and purchase of securities; (6) other capital movements, for (a) all countries; (b) United Kingdom; (c) other sterling areas; (d) United States of America; (6) all other countries?
